"Report back to me at the Office"
"Site B is looking pretty horrible. I need you to use the modeling and simulation tool to determine the likely fate of the ecosystem there."
"Collect population data from the Site B Critters"
"Collect data from the Site B Research Probe"
"Build a Model to Predict the future for Site B"

"Let's use everything you have learned so far to save the Urchin Barren. Use the model you made to try out potential interventions and simulate the long term outcomes. Tell me if you find any potential solutions for resoring Site B."
"Make a plan for how to save the Urchin Barren"
"Tell Dr. Jules about your plan in the office"
"Site R is in trouble. We need you to figure out what's going on.\nWho is invading this coral reef?"
"Figure out what is invading Site R"
"Use the Stress Tank to determine what's affecting the Staghorn Coral"
"Collect historical light data from Site R"
"Tell Professor Cempaka what's up with the Staghorn Coral"
"We need your help figuring out if Sargassum is to blame. Use your tools to figure out how it may be effecting the ecosystem.\nShould the Sargassum be removed?"
"Find out what Sargassum does to the environment"
"Model Sargassum's impact on the Staghorn Coral"
"We don't know how Sargassum fits into the food web at site R. Find out if anything might eat it up and get it out of here.\nShould the Sargassum be cleared out from the environment?"
"Identify Sargassum's relationships to other critters in the reef"
"Find an organism that might eat it"
"We heard about how you used modeling and simulation to propose a solution to the Urchin Barren. What would happen if we introduced Urchins at Site R?\nAre the Urchins friends or foes?"
"Assess Model of Urchins in Site R"
"Find out whether urchins would be stressed in the reef"
"Build a Model to Predict the Future of Site R"
"Site V is a very popular fishing spot for Grouper. We need to set some guidelines for how much fishing can be done sustainably. \nHow much Red Grouper can be harvested sustainably?"
"Visit the Fisherman's Boat to gather data"
"Scan at Site V to find Red Grouper's Reproduction and Fishing Rates"
"Build a model to determine how many boats can be licensed to fish"
"Why is the shrimp catch going down?"
"The oxygen levels seemed pretty low.  What implications might that have concerning the shrimp situation?"
"See if there's a significant relationship between shrimp and oxygen levels."
"Report back about the shrimp oxygen consumption."
"Some researchers down south counted the pod on arrival and one is missing. They think she got lost up here."
"Search Sites Z and W for signs of the missing whale"

"Search the ice for signs of microscopic life"
"How long ago did the missing whale die?"
"Scan and Tag all critters at Site W"
"The urchin barren had Urchins and Giant Kelp. Simulate how these populations will change over time."
"Prediciton successful. The simulator shows that the urchin barren at Site B is only going to get worse."
"Can an urchin barren be repaired? Use what you've learned from healthy Kelp Forests to intervene with the Urchin Baren
"Intervention successful. The simulator shows that the urchin barren can be repaired by releasing sea otters."
"Is an urchin barren likely to occur in the cool kelp forest?"
"Prediction successful. Ecosystem is sustainable for the forseeable future."
"How does Sargassum change the light levels and affect the Staghorn Coral?"
"Prediciton successful. The simulator shows Sargassum reduces the light to levels dangerous to Staghorn Coral."
"How does the number of Fishers affect the Red Grouper population?"
"Prediciton successful. The simulator shows up to 40 Fishers can safely sustain the Red Grouper population."
